						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Parāntaka I, 30th year = A.D. 937.</p>						

						<p>A gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">chey</hi> of land for a lamp by a Eṟumbiyūr-uḍaiyāṉ Nakka-nāgaṉ to the temple of Teṉkayilāyattu-Mahādēva at Śrīkaṇṭha-chaturvēdimaṅgalam. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the village made the land tax-free after receiving the tax capital.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIII, No. 166.)</p>						

